# Framework runtime artifacts — generated per session, never source.
# The orchestration framework relies on these staying OUT of git (CLAUDE.md: "Notes are
# local only — never committed to git"), but a project bootstrapped from this template
# needs the rule too. Greenfield projects get this file as-is; an existing project with its
# own .gitignore should MERGE these lines in (see the bootstrap protocol) rather than
# overwrite. Add your project's own ignores (node_modules/, dist/, .env, …) below.

# Agent working memory: chain manifest, per-agent notes, chain log, backups.
.agentNotes/

# Read-only agent report artifacts (hunter et al.) — regenerated, not source.
reports/hunter/

# Claude Code local, user-specific settings (permissions, machine paths).
.claude/settings.local.json
